headline: Texas Instruments (TXN): Valuation Reassessed After China Launches Chipmaker Investigations
summary: Texas Instruments (TXN) is suddenly in the spotlight after China's Ministry of Commerce launched anti-dumping and discrimination investigations specifically targeting U.S. chipmakers, including TXN itself. These probes arrive on the heels of louder trade tensions between the U.S. and China and have instantly ramped up uncertainty for any American semiconductor company with exposure to the region.
